#. <section class="sutta" id="an7.37"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an7.37:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 7"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 7"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an7.37:0.2"
msgid "4. devatāvagga"
msgstr "4. Deities"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 37. Dutiyamittasutta → bhikkhumittasuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an7.37:0.3"
msgid "37. Dutiyamittasutta"
msgstr "37. A Friend"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.32"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an7.37:1.1"
msgid ""
"“Sattahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu mitto sevitabbo bhajitabbo "
"payirupāsitabbo api panujjamānenapi."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, when a friend has seven qualities you should associate with, "
"accompany, and attend them, even if they send you away."

msgctxt "an7.37:1.2"
msgid "Katamehi sattahi?"
msgstr "What seven?"

# See BB’s note on vattā. I think the point of the comm’s “vacanakusala” is that “vacana” is frequently used idiomatically in the sense of “admonish, criticize”. Thus it pairs with vacanakkhamo.
msgctxt "an7.37:1.3"
msgid ""
"Piyo ca hoti manāpo ca garu ca bhāvanīyo ca vattā ca vacanakkhamo ca "
"gambhīrañca kathaṃ kattā hoti, no ca aṭṭhāne niyojeti."
msgstr ""
"They’re likable, agreeable, respected, and admired. They admonish you and "
"they accept admonishment. They speak on deep matters. And they don’t urge "
"you to do bad things."

msgctxt "an7.37:1.4"
msgid ""
"Imehi kho, bhikkhave, sattahi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu mitto sevitabbo "
"bhajitabbo payirupāsitabbo api panujjamānenapīti."
msgstr ""
"When a friend has these seven qualities you should associate with, "
"accompany, and attend with them, even if they send you away.”"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an7.37:2.1"
msgid "Piyo garu bhāvanīyo,"
msgstr "“They’re lovable, respected, and admired,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an7.37:2.2"
msgid "vattā ca vacanakkhamo;"
msgstr "an admonisher who accepts admonishment,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an7.37:2.3"
msgid "Gambhīrañca kathaṃ kattā,"
msgstr "speaks on deep matters,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: niyojako → niyojaye (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "an7.37:2.4"
msgid "no caṭṭhāne niyojako."
msgstr "and doesn’t urge you to do bad."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an7.37:3.1"
msgid "Yamhi etāni ṭhānāni,"
msgstr "The person in whom"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an7.37:3.2"
msgid "saṃvijjantīdha puggale;"
msgstr "these things are found is your friend."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an7.37:3.3"
msgid "So mitto mittakāmena,"
msgstr "If you want to have a friend,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an7.37:3.4"
msgid "atthakāmānukampato;"
msgstr "benevolent and compassionate,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an7.37:3.5"
msgid "Api nāsiyamānena,"
msgstr "you should keep company with such a person,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an7.37:3.6"
msgid "bhajitabbo tathāvidho”ti."
msgstr "even if they send you away.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an7.37:3.7"
msgid "Chaṭṭhaṃ."
msgstr ""
